news.title: West Bengal plans four new IT parks
news.para: State IT and electronics minister Babul Supriyo said: "We are focusing on development of IT infrastructure in north Bengal in a big way.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh cabinet approves green law for eco-friendly ULBs
news.para: Under this policy, a Green City Monitoring System will be developed to evaluate and award Green Star ratings to cities based on their environmental efforts and green infrastructure.

news.title: Gujarat government allots ₹3,395 crore to urban civic bodies for development projects
news.para: An official statement said that a sum of Rs 3,263 crore was sanctioned for the Surat Municipal Corporation, while Nadiad Municipal Corporation was provided a sum of Rs 45 crore.

news.title: Karnataka: 1% stamp duty hike likely to overcome property revenue shortfall in Q1 FY26
news.para: At present, the govt levies 5% stamp duty on the guidance value (minimum selling price of property fixed by the govt), 1% registration fee, 0.5% cess, and 0.1% surcharge. In all, property buyers pay 6.6% in cess and duty. They might end up 7.6% if the govt clears the hike proposal.

news.title: Goa government loses ₹107 crore as TCP gives free FAR to 321 commercial units
news.para: The TCP department granted 10.7 lakh sqm additional FAR to 321 commercial establishments on their request without levying any fees, while the finance department had directed the TCP to charge Rs 1,000 per sqm on the additional FAR and height granted to the commercial establishments.

news.title: Kolkata: Police involve RWAs in New Town, neighbouring areas for tenant check
news.para: ​If the list does not match the database available with the police, they are calling up the landlords and tenants to immediately fill up a KYC verification form or face a penalty.

news.title: Mohali development body auctions 24% of plots on offer, earns ₹136 crore
news.para: Among residential properties, two 500-square-yard plots in Sector 82, Alpha Block-B, IT City, sold for Rs 6.87 crore each, above their reserve price of Rs 6.35 crore. A 300-square-yard plot in Block-A of Ecocity-1 also fetched Rs 3.5 crore, compared to its reserve price of Rs 3 crore.

news.title: Nagpur: Kamptee’s British-era bungalows not for sale without approval of army
news.para: The instructions were issued last week by the joint registrar to the registration offices down the line. The OGBs are classified as B-3 defence land.

news.title: NCC Urban forays into Mumbai realty market with redevelopment project in Versova
news.para: NCC Urban Infrastructure Limited has entered Mumbai's property market. They are starting with a redevelopment project in Versova. The project has a development potential of 4 lakh sq ft. It is expected to generate revenue of approximately Rs 700 crore. This project aligns with the company's expansion strategy. NCC Urban aims to explore more opportunities in western India.

news.title: Himachal HC imposes penalty for delay in RERA appointment
news.para: "The government is playing hide and seek first, citing the relocation of RERA headquarters to Dharamshala, and now delaying appointments under the pretext of procedural issues," the bench remarked.

news.title: UK's Berkeley appoints Rob Perrins as executive chair to lead growth strategy​
news.para: Shares in the high-end home builder dropped 8% and were headed for their worst day since March 2020, as it also reported results and forecast fiscal 2026 and 2027 profit below market expectations as affordability concerns weigh on the sector.

news.title: SC tells Delhi HC to expeditiously decide DHFL ex-promoter's bail plea
news.para: A bench of Justices Ujjal Bhuyan and Manmohan said Wadhawan was in custody since July, 2022 and his bail plea was coming up for hearing on July 18 in the high court.

news.title: Cognizant to invest $183 million for to build new campus in Vishakapatanam
news.para: Commercial operations will begin in March 2029, an Andhra Pradesh government press release said. Cognizant did not immediately respond to a request for comment.

news.title: Kalpataru sells properties worth ₹2,727 crore in Apr-Dec FY25
news.para: The company sold properties worth Rs 3,201.98 crore in 2023-24, according to its updated red herring prospectus (RHP) filed with Sebi. The latest document has updates till the third quarter of the 2024-25 fiscal only.

news.title: Innov8 sells 3% stake at ₹1,000 crore valuation to expand co-working business
news.para: Raymond Family Office has emerged as the lead investor, acquiring nearly 2 per cent share, they added. Global travel tech platform OYO Group declined to comment.

news.title: Pune: PCMC cancels Charholi town planning scheme after CM’s directive
news.para: Civic officials said the proposal to cancel the TP schemes was approved in the general body meeting by municipal commissioner and administrator Shekhar Singh on Wednesday.

news.title: Lucknow: LDA set to develop 10 sectors, grid road too in IT City soon
news.para: LDA vice chairperson Prathamesh Kumar handed over the agreement deed at the authority office. Notably, 39 landowners from five villages have offered around 186 acres of land under the land pooling scheme.

news.title: Delhi government likely to study Mumbai's Dharavi model for slum redevelopment
news.para: "If you construct a house near a railway line, the chief minister will not save you. I urge people to think about safety and security. If a railway accident happens or someone dies on the railway track, who will be responsible?" she said.

news.title: Nine teams to inspect illegal buildings: Thane civic body to Bombay HC
news.para: Justices Girish Kulkarni and Arif Doctor were hearing a petition by senior citizen Subhadra Takle regarding 17 buildings that were erected by land mafia who had usurped her 5.5 acre property at Shil village. On June 12, HC ordered immediate site inspection by a court officer and a judicial inquiry.
